---
import { Link } from "../../lib/Link";
import { Paragraph } from "../prose/Paragraph";
---

<script src="./animation.ts"></script>

<div id="world"></div>
<div class="" id="homeWorld">
  <div class="min-h-screen overflow-auto relative">
    <h1
      id="name"
      class="absolute top-[40%] flex items-center justify-center w-full text-center left-1/2 xl:text-7xl text-3xl text-white font-bold -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"
      style="display: none;"
    >
      Siddharth Suresh
    </h1>

    <p
      id="description"
      class="absolute flex w-full flex-col bottom-[18%] left-1/2 xl:text-2xl text-sm text-center text-white font-bold -translate-x-1/2 translate-y-1/2"
    >
      Full Stack Developer & Open Source Enthusiast
    </p>
  </div>

  <div
    class="min-h-screen bg-[#224b69cb] xl:p-16 p-3 rounded-3xl"
    id="vprojects"
  >
    <p
      id="viewProjects"
      class="xl:text-4xl lg:text-2xl md:text-lg text-md text-white font-bold text-start p-10"
    >
      About Me
    </p>
    <div
      class="flex xl:flex-row flex-col items-center justify-around gap-10 xl:text-xl text-sm"
    >
      <div class="xl:w-[60%]">
        <Paragraph class="mt-6 xl:text-justify leading-8">
          Hey there! I'm Siddharth Suresh. I am full stack developer and a
          student at Vellore Institute of Technology, Chennai pursuing
          B.Tech in Computer Science with a Specialization in Cyber Physical
          Systems.
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph class="mt-6 xl:text-justify leading-8">
          I'm excited to share my journey as a TypeScript Full Stack
          Developer and my contributions to the open-source community,
          particularly my work as a Core Team Member and Maintainer of
          <Link href="https://www.blitzjs.com">âš¡ Blitz.js</Link> .
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph class="mt-6 xl:text-justify leading-8">
          As a developer, I have a strong foundation in Data Structures and
          Algorithms which has helped me develop the skills necessary to
          solve complex problems and build efficient systems. I am constantly
          looking for new challenges and am always eager to learn new
          technologies, which makes me passionate about languages and frameworks such as Rust
          and Phoenix (Elixir).
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph class="mt-6 xl:text-justify leading-8" id="aboutMe">
          I'll be sharing my experiences, insights, and learnings as a emerging
          TypeScript Full Stack Developer, as well as my journey as a
          contributor to the open-source community in the form of blog posts.
        </Paragraph>
      </div>
      <div class="xl:w-1/3 flex flex-col gap-10 items-center justify-center">
        <Paragraph
          class="xl:text-2xl lg:text-xl md:text-lg text-md font-bold text-center"
        >
          My Tech Stack
        </Paragraph>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-16">
          <img src="/logos/nextjs.png" />
          <img src="/logos/blitz.png" />
          <img src="/logos/react.png" />
          <img src="/logos/tanstack.png" />
          <img src="/logos/tailwind.png" />
          <img src="/logos/prisma.png" />
          <img src="/logos/typescript.png" />
          <img src="/logos/eslint.png" />
          <img src="/logos/vscode.png" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="tooltip"></div>

<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Source+Code+Pro:ital,wght@1,900&display=swap');
  h1,
  p {
    font-family: 'Source Code Pro', monospace;
    color: #fff;
  }

  #world {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: linear-gradient(#164b60, #1b6b93);
    z-index: -1;
    /* make world stay as is while scrolling */
    transform: translateZ(0);
  }

  #tooltip {
    display: none;
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    background: #104b68da;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0.5rem rgb(0, 0, 0);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: white;
  }
</style>
